The majority of women in Slovakia view divorce as a positive experience, according to a survey conducted by the Institute for Public Affairs (IVO) in cooperation with the Institute for Research of the Slovak Academy of Sciences (ÚVZ) and the Slovak Academy of Sciences (SAV).

The survey was conducted in 2009 on a sample of 1,000 women aged 18 to 65. It showed that 60 percent of women who had been divorced viewed the experience as positive, while 40 percent viewed it as negative. The survey also showed that 60 percent of divorced women were satisfied with their lives, while 40 percent were not.
